Jonathan R. Mather  Chief Financial Officer and Secretary, ERS Digital Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 4 different industries.66--
Background

		Mr. Jonathan R. Mather serves as the Chief Financial Officer and Secretary of ERS Digital Inc. Mr. Mather served as the Chief Financial Officer of ARC Document Solutions, Inc. from December 2006 to July 8, 2011. Since retiring in 2011, he has served as a Consultant to a private equity firm and startup companies. He served as Secretary and Principal Accounting Officer of ARC Document Solutions, Inc. until April 2011. He served as an Executive Vice President of Netgear ... Inc. from October 2003 to November 30, 2006 and served as its Principal Accounting Officer until November 30, 2006. He served as Vice President of Netgear Inc. from August 2001 to October 2003. He served as Netgear's Chief Financial Officer from August 2001 to November 30, 2006. From July 1995 to March 2001, Mr. Mather worked at Applause Inc., a consumer products company, where he served as President and Chief Executive Officer from 1998 to 2001, as Chief Operating Officer from 1997 to 1998 and as Chief Financial Officer from 1995 to 1997. From 1985 to 1995, he was at Home Fashions Inc., a consumer products company, where he served as Chief Financial Officer from 1992 to 1995 and as Vice President, finance of an operating division, Louverdrape, from 1988 to 1992. Prior to that, he spent more than two years at the semiconductor division of Harris Corporation, a communications equipment company, where he served as the finance manager of the offshore manufacturing division. He has also worked in public accounting for four years with Coopers & Lybrand (now part of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP) and for two years with Ernst & Young. He served as a Director of Spark Networks, Inc. since September 12, 2014 until March 13, 2017. Mr. Mather began his career in public accounting, working for four years with Coopers & Lybrand International (now part of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP) and for two years with Ernst & Young. He is a certified management accountant (CMA) and is also a Chartered Accountant from the Institute of Chartered Accountants in Sri Lanka, where he received his undergraduate B.A. degree equivalent. Mr. Mather received an M.B.A. from Cornell University, New York, in 1983.Read Full Background




